net.sf.mmm.util.value.api

Class Range<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.value.api.Range<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - is the generic type of the contained values.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AttributeReadMaximumValue<V>, AttributeReadMinimumValue<V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NumberRange

    public class Range<V>
extends Object
implements Serializable, AttributeReadMinimumValue<V>, AttributeReadMaximumValue<V>
    This class represents a range of two values, minimum and maximum. Validation is performed at construction so a given Range should always be valid (unless created via reflection or de-serialization).
    ATTENTION:
    Since version 4.0.0 the minimum and maximum value may be null for unbounded ranges. It is still recommended to use fixed bounds such as Long.MAX_VALUE. However, for types such as BigDecimal this is not possible.
    Since:
    3.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
